In article <1993Nov24.220503.18313@mnemosyne.cs.du.edu>, astrashe@nyx10.cs.du.edu (Alex Strasheim) writes:
|> 
|> I'm trying to understand Chaum's scheme for blinded signatures, and I was 
|> wondering if anyone could point me to a description of the mathematics 
|> involved or perhaps some code.

Ok, here are a few references:

R. L. Rivest, A. Shamir and L. Adleman,
"A Method for Obtaining Digital Signatures and Public-Key Cryptosystems",
Communications of the ACM,
Vol. 21, No. 2, pp. 120-126, February, 1978.

Martin E. Hellman,
"The Mathematics of Public-Key Cryptography",
Scientific American,
Vol. 241, No. 2, pp. 130-139, August 1979.

D. W. Davies and W. L. Price,
"Security for Computer Networks",
Wiley, second edition, 1989.

